{"id": "EUVD-2025-205214", "enisaUuid": "b056bad5-6924-3da5-9664-7830ba1b62b1", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/panthor: Fix UAF race between device unplug and FW event processing\n\nThe function panthor_fw_unplug() will free the FW memory sections.\nThe problem is that there could still be pending FW events which are yet\nnot handled at this point. process_fw_events_work() can in this case try\nto access said freed memory.\n\nSimply call disable_work_sync() to both drain and prevent future\ninvocation of process_fw_events_work().", "datePublished": "2025-12-24T15:30:44", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-24T15:30:44", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/31db188355a49337e3e8ec98b99377e482eab22c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5e3ff56d4cb591daea70786d07dc21d06dc34108", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6c1da9ae2c123a9ffda5375e64cc81f9ed3cc04a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7051f6ba968fa69918d72cc26de4d6cf7ea05b90", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-68748"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-68748"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "3800b803-cf2b-3094-a362-140f28e5df56", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "de85488138247d034eb3241840424a54d660926b <31db188355a49337e3e8ec98b99377e482eab22c"}, {"id": "3b9feca6-8af4-3158-a412-3687fbeb5813", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "de85488138247d034eb3241840424a54d660926b <7051f6ba968fa69918d72cc26de4d6cf7ea05b90"}, {"id": "43e6253d-219c-3694-9ab3-37dbd199b277", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "de85488138247d034eb3241840424a54d660926b <6c1da9ae2c123a9ffda5375e64cc81f9ed3cc04a"}, {"id": "53bcfadb-81eb-3ef4-8d0c-a77362643413", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17.13"}, {"id": "6132cf83-4b26-3f36-8479-da3f9c2896fe", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.63"}, {"id": "61e84753-761d-30a4-a7ac-79e5d333cf7e", "product": {"name": "Lin